<!-- Displaying desktop network questions -->
<div id="desktopNetworkDr" class="display-header">
    <h5><a href="#desktopContent" data-toggle="collapse">Desktop/Network/DR
            <i class="fa fa-arrows-v" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
    </h5>
    <br>

    <div id="desktopContent" class="collapse">
        <div class="edit pull-right">
            <a href="#" aria-hidden="true" data-target="#editDesktopNetwork" data-toggle="modal">
                <i class="fa fa-pencil-square-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>Edit</a>
        </div>
        <br>

        <h5><a href="#desktop-Network" style="color: mediumvioletred" data-toggle="collapse">Network & Security
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
        </h5>

        <!-- Network and security -->
        <div id="desktop-Network" class="collapse">
            <div id="networkSecurity" class="row">
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you want users to be able to access the user interface outside of your
                            network?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.allow_outside_access %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>DMZ</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.DMZ %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Firewalls</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.firewalls %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>VPN Connection to PFPT Required</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.require_vpn %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Enable access to user outside network</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.enable_outside_access %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Load Balancer/VIP</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.load_balancer_VIP %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>NAT IP List</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.nat_IP_list %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Proxy Servers</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.network_security.proxy_servers %></p></div>
            </div>
            <br>
        </div>

        <!-- End user desktop env -->
        <h5><a href="#desktop-End-User" style="color: mediumvioletred" data-toggle="collapse">End User Desktop Environment
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
        </h5>

        <div id="desktop-End-User" class="collapse">
            <div id="endUserEnv" class="row">
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>What browsers do user have access to (Chrome, IE, Edge, Firefox, etc.)?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.browsers %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>What versions of each available browsers are allowed</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.browser_versions %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you run IE 11</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.ie11 %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Can users enable compatibility mode in IE 11</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.ie11_compatibility %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Is IE deployed in Enterprise Mode?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.is_ie11_enterprise %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Can users enable pop-ups for specific URLs</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.is_popups_enabled %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do users use OWA?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.is_OWA_used %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do users have access to: Chrome/Firefox/Edge (Not sure about question)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.end_user_desktop_env.browsers_access %></p></div>
            </div>
            <br>
        </div>

        <!-- Disaster Recovery -->
        <h5><a href="#desktop-Disaster" style="color: mediumvioletred" data-toggle="collapse">Disaster Recovery / High Probability
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
        </h5>

        <div id="desktop-Disaster" class="collapse">
            <div id="disasterRecovery" class="row">
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you have Exchange and AD being replicated to a secondary data center</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.disaster_recovery.is_replicating_exchange_and_AD %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Describe what does the DR/HA configuration look like.</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.disaster_recovery.config_description %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Can you provide a diagram of the Exchange environment with the DR/HA
                            included.
                            (File
                            upload???)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.disaster_recovery.diagram %></p></div>
            </div>
            <br>
        </div>

        <h5><a href="#desktop-Auth" style="color: mediumvioletred" data-toggle="collapse">Authentication (SAML & Remote Auth)
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
        </h5>

        <div id="desktop-Auth" class="collapse">
            <div id="authentication" class="row">
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you use SSO?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.use_SSO %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you have an IDP (Identity Provider) that supports SAML 2.0?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.have_IDP %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Where will the PFPT AD security groups be maintained? (On prem deployments
                            require
                            universal
                            groups containing all users that need to log in, in the resource forest)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.where_security_group %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Service provider or IDP (Identity Provider) initiated? (we only support
                            Service
                            Provider
                            initiated)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.intiated_IDP %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you require request encryption? (we don't support it)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.require_request_encryption %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you require response signing? (we support it)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.require_response_signing %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you require response encryption? (we support it)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.require_response_encryption %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>If the response is to be encrypted, do you require a 3rd party cert or is a
                            self-signed
                            cert
                            sufficient? We support both</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.require_third_party_cert %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>What attribute will you be sending as part of the response? (we only support
                            UPN,
                            email,
                            and
                            SID)</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.response_attributes %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Do you intend to deploy PFPT's remote authentication?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.intend_to_deploy_remote_auth %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Are all user accounts on trusted forests?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.all_users_trusted %></p></div>
                <div id="" class="col-4 response-cell"><p><b>Are all domain controllers accessible on the same network as the server that
                            Remote
                            Auth
                            will
                            be installed?</b>
                        <br><%= desktop_network_questions.authentication.domain_controllers %></p></div>
            </div>
            <br>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<hr class="rainbow">

